How to Apply Proper Risk Management in Trading

One of the most important keys to long-term trading success is proper risk managementâ€”and it doesnâ€™t have to be complicated.

Hereâ€™s a simple example to guide you:
Letâ€™s say you start with $1000.

- On your first trade, you risk 1%, which is $10, and you make a $20 profit. Now your balance is $1020.

- Next, you decide to risk $15. This trade earns you $30, bringing your total to $1050.

- Third trade, you risk $20, but it's a loss. Your balance drops to $1030.
Now you reduce your risk by halfâ€”$10â€”but it's another loss, so youâ€™re at $1020.

- Final trade, you risk just $5, and make a $10 profit, bringing your account to $1030.

As you can see, even with two losing trades, your account is still growingâ€”because your risk was controlled and your profits were allowed to accumulate smartly.

This is just one simple approachâ€”you can always adapt it to your own style and strategy. The key idea is this:
Never risk too much. Stay consistent. Adjust as your account grows or shrinks.

https://youtu.be/zgaYnm5Yvyo?si=Tw48sdhbgn7s1ZBq

Smart risk management keeps you in the game when others are blowing their accounts.

Stay sharp, stay disciplined, and trade wisely my friends!
